🌐 Browser Storage (Cookies vs Local Storage vs Session Storage)
Module: Web Security
Lesson: Day 10

Introduction
Modern web applications need to store information inside the user's browser.

Examples include:

Login sessions
User preferences
Language settings
Shopping carts
JWT tokens
Browsers provide multiple storage mechanisms for this purpose.

The three most common are:

Cookies
Local Storage
Session Storage
Although all three store data inside the browser, they behave very differently.

Understanding these differences is important because attackers often target browser storage to steal sensitive information.

Browser Storage Overview
