Each storage type has different properties and security implications.

Cookies
A Cookie is a small piece of data stored inside the browser.

The server usually creates cookies using:

Set-Cookie:

session=abc123
The browser stores:

session=abc123
Every future request automatically includes:

Cookie:

session=abc123
This is why cookies are commonly used for authentication.

Cookie Characteristics
Cookies:

Stored inside the browser
Automatically sent with every HTTP request to the same website
Can have an expiration date
Usually store Session IDs
Support security attributes
Security attributes include:

